# Vnansial — All-in-one Indonesian Financial Platform
Priority: P0
Status: in_progress
Last updated: 2026-05-15

## Goal
Turn Vnansial into a single, open-source, locally-runnable financial platform
where Indonesians get:
- IDX saham coverage (semua emiten Indonesia, profile, dividen, laporan
  keuangan, ESG, history, pemegang saham, kalender)
- Crypto watch with scam/fraud risk probability
- Insurance information, recommendations, premium calculator
- Personal finance: portfolio, savings, emergency fund, money buffer,
  kesehatan finansial
- AI Asisten that uses all of the above via tool-calling
- Telegram bot so the user can talk to their data from chat
- SQLite persistence for portfolio + score history + telegram binding

## Why
The earlier rebuild made the UI calm and bento-driven. The user now wants the
*content* to match: real Indonesian data sources, complete asset coverage,
and the same calm bento navigation pattern carried through.

## Architecture decisions
1. **Server proxies** for everything that has CORS or fragile public APIs
   (idx.co.id requires a Referer header; CoinGecko works direct but
   centralising lets us rate-limit & cache).
2. **SQLite via `better-sqlite3`** for portfolio + health snapshots + telegram
   bindings. Sync API → trivial to use, no migrations framework needed.
3. **Telegram bot via raw HTTP API** (no extra dep). Env-gated by
   `TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN`; polling mode for local dev, webhook ready.
4. **Local-first** — every feature works against localStorage if the server
   is offline. SQLite is the upgrade path for self-hosters.
5. **Navbar-less home** — Landing becomes the bento command center; other
   pages keep a minimal top bar with logo + Home.
6. **Open source friendly** — CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, CONTRIBUTING.md so any
   AI coding agent can pick up the codebase consistently.

## New server modules
- `server/lib/idx.js` — IDX.co.id proxy with Referer header + cache
- `server/lib/coingecko.js` — Crypto data + scam heuristic
- `server/lib/insurance.js` — Indonesian insurance data (BPJS, swasta)
- `server/lib/db.js` — SQLite layer (graceful fallback)
- `server/integrations/telegram.js` — Bot polling + commands
- `server/tools/idx.js`, `server/tools/crypto.js`, `server/tools/insurance.js`,
  `server/tools/portfolio.js` — agent-callable wrappers

## New frontend pages
- `/emiten` — Cek Emiten (IDX) with profile, financial chart, dividen
- `/crypto` — CryptoWatch with risk badge
- `/asuransi` — Insurance comparator + premium calculator
- `/portofolio` — Portfolio + savings + emergency fund manager

## New agent tools
- `get_idx_company_profile` (KodeEmiten)
- `get_idx_financial_report` (KodeEmiten, periode, year)
- `get_idx_dividen` (KodeEmiten, year)
- `list_idx_emiten` (optional search)
- `get_crypto_quote` (symbol/id)
- `assess_crypto_scam_risk` (symbol/id)
- `recommend_insurance` (riskProfile, budget, dependents)
- `calculate_insurance_premium` (type, coverage, age)
- `get_user_portfolio` / `save_portfolio_holding`

## Phases (mapped to `.progress/super-platform.progress`)
1. Plan + progress files
2. Server libs (idx, coingecko, insurance, db, telegram)
3. Server tools + endpoints + definitions wiring
4. Frontend pages (Emiten, Crypto, Asuransi, Portofolio)
5. Landing refactor (nav-less, bento)
6. Contributor docs (CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, CONTRIBUTING.md, ARCHITECTURE.md)
7. Tests + build

## Out of scope (this iteration)
- User auth (single-user assumption for local self-host)
- WebSocket live price streaming
- Bond marketplace (data added to insurance/edukasi only)
